item.title: Hello world!
item.dc:creator: landing_master
item.content:encoded: Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start writing!

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: Hi, this is a comment. To get started with moderating, editing, and deleting comments, please visit the Comments screen in the dashboard. Commenter avatars come from Gravatar.

item.title: Sample Page
item.dc:creator: landing_master
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

item.title: About the business
item.dc:creator: landing_master
item.content:encoded:
• What kind of business leads the company?
  • What is the typical customer of the company?
  • What is the target audience of the company?
  • Who are the main partners of the company?
  • Who are the main competitors of the company?
  • What are the unique properties of the goods / services of the company?

item.title: About preferences
item.dc:creator: landing_master
item.content:encoded:
• What is the highest priority: the quality or speed?
  • Does the company have a corporate identity?
  • What sites are the closest match to the expectations? Show 3 sites
  • What style is preferred and why?
  • What color scheme would like to use in the design?
  • What graphic elements you want to use in the design?
  • Stretched or fixed design do you prefer?
  • Can I use subcontractors or outsourcing the project?

item.title: About the project
item.dc:creator: landing_master
item.content:encoded:
• What is the budget for this project?
  • What is the deadline for this project?
  • How the payment will take place?
  • How often planned upgrades or additions to your site?
  • Who will be maintaining your website?
  • Will it be you, your admin team, or will you be working with a vendor?
  • Determine the technical skill level of the people who will be maintaining the site and what kind of updates will be made on a regular basis.
  • What functionality does your site need? Differentiate between "needs" and "wants". What does your website absolutely need to do in order to meet your goals?

item.title: And so on
item.dc:creator: landing_master
item.content:encoded:
• Do I need to provide additional design options?
  • Do I need to create a new process or additional graphics or illustrations?
  • Do I need to run something else for a single style: business cards, logos, etc.?
  • Can you recommend someone use my services?
  • Are you interested in my consultations on issues related to the Internet?

item.title: About the structure of the site
item.dc:creator: landing_master
item.content:encoded:
• What sections will have a website?
  • What are the main units will have a website?
  • What information will be on the site?
  • What content services will be integrated into the site?
  • What kind of feedback forms will be on the site?
  • Will the interactive elements of the site: the gallery?

item.title: About materials
item.dc:creator: landing_master
item.content:encoded:
• What text materials can be provided?
  • What kind of graphics can be presented?
  • What printed or multimedia materials can be presented?
  • Which may still be useful in the process?
